Rating: 4
Wow! Made this tonight, and I must say it is the best beef stew I have ever made. I made it exactly by the recipe, and would recommend doing this per the recipe-do not use a broth of any kind unless you plan to leave out the salt or you will ruin the dish. The amount of salt called for in the recipe is on the edge of what is too salty for my taste, but it is saved by the fresh parsley and orange zest garnish. I will definitely be making this again and again, and the only change I will make is to cut back slightly on the salt. This is not a recipe to make if you are missing any of the ingredients-it's success depends on having the right blend and freshness of flavor. This should warm up many a cold winter's night to come.

