Wow, this was good. I usually start by making the recipe as written , but this time, since I was doubling it, felt a couple of small adjustments were a good idea: First, half the cinnamon sticks. Second, used some stock instead of the water. The results were excellent. Next time, I think I'll use a bit less vinegar; don't get me wrong: you DO NOT taste the vinegar when all is said and done, but there is a bit of sharpness we'd rather be less. I did not feel adding more wine or veg was necessary; the taste was an overall success. Using half of the cinnamon (for a double recipe, remember) gave the stew a subtle taste of cinnamon which we thought was a home run.

