Rating: 4
I served this to a crowd of people last week and it was a unanimous hit! Even those who don't usually eat seconds had some (one person even had a third serving), and they were still talking about it two days later. The recipe double easily. Because none of us are a fan of stews served over something else (potato, rice, noodles), I put small red potatoes in the stew, used beef broth instead of water, and then added about a 1/3rd of a bottle of red wine so that there would be a little more liquid in the stew. I also cut the veggies larger so that they wouldn't disintegrate into the liquid. I will admit I was a bit sceptical about the cinnamon, but it absolutely made the stew. Like others, I also doubled the herbs. This stew was so unique an flavourful, particularly with the orange zest! I will be making this stew again and again.

Rating: 4
I've made this a couple times now and its a HUGE hit with the family. I followed some hints from other reviewers and also tried a few of my own. My changes include: a) doubling the carrots and celery and adding 2 parsnips and 3/4 C baby bella mushrooms, b) increasing the wine to ~ 1 cup, c) tying up the sage, rosemary and thyme in cheesecloth to eliminate the leaves falling off the stems into the stew, d) substituting 1 cup of beef broth for one of the cups of water e) using 1 tsp of salt. I let it cook about 1 1/2 - 2 hours and serve over egg noodles. Enjoy!

