Rating: 4
Outstanding. The orange zest is a wonderful brightener, and the spices and herbs are ideal. However: first time I made this, I braised the dish for nearly three hours, let it sit (dinner was hours away) and then re- heated and zested. The meat was buttery soft and falling apart, yet thickly glazed with that rich sauce. The second time, I served it right away (no sitting or reheating). Now we all know braises like this tend to taste better on re-heating. But the consistency of the meat was also very different. In short, the first approach worked better, making for a much more tender braise as well as better flavor.

