Rating: 4
I cooked this recipe as written with a few alterations - I substituted the sage for dried oregano, added bell pepper and some red pepper flakes, and added an extra half leek and carrot. This recipe will not yield the traditional savory, meaty broth you might be used to. Instead, the herbs and wine are the stars in the sauce. It is fruity and not too heavy. This stew is great served over egg noodles or accompanied with roasted potatoes you can make with the leftover fresh herbs. It's a nice change from other beef stew recipes as its flavor notes are more complex than just "meat and potatoes." A few days after trying this recipe, my family demanded I make it again - this time doubled for extra leftovers!

